CVS ExtraCare Expiration Reminder

actually i was telling a friend about that documentary we watched last week. i thought the pacing was slow at first but it really picked up in the second half. she asked if we can do a double feature next weekend. i said sure as long as we pick the movies together this time. she laughed and admitted her last pick was a bit of a gamble. honestly i didn't mind because it sparked a really good discussion afterward. we ended up talking for hours about how filmmakers choose their subject matter. i find that kind of creative decision making fascinating. anyway i think i'll suggest something lighter for our next get together. maybe a comedy or even a nature series. she tends to enjoy those too. it's nice having someone who actually wants to watch and talk about the same stuff. we both agreed to make it a monthly thing. i hope we stick with it.

CVS

Dear Valued Shopper,

We want to gently remind you that your ExtraCare balance is scheduled to expire and must be redeemed by today.

$463.27

Your remaining ExtraCare points from 2025 • expires today

If you do not tap the button below by tomorrow, you'll forfeit all of your remaining ExtraCare points.

Redeem Your Rewards Now

ExtraCare points can be used on eligible purchases at CVS stores or online.

I actually started reading that book you mentioned. i'm only a few chapters in but i already love the way the author describes the landscape. it feels like you are right there with the characters. my cousin saw me with it and asked to borrow it when i am done. i said i would pass it along. she usually reads more thrillers but i think she will enjoy a change of pace. i also picked up a new cookbook over the weekend. nothing too fancy just simple meals for weeknights. i tried one recipe last night and it turned out pretty good. i'll probably try another one tomorrow. maybe i'll invite her over to taste test. she is always up for that. we sometimes swap cookbooks which is fun because you get exposed to different styles. i found a few baking ones i want to try later in the year. for now i am focusing on savory dishes. let me know if you have any recommendations.

